<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-01-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-01-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="743" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d743">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.48/3827: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mexico City</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Frazer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-01-15T13:00:00-07:00">January 15, 1931—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 2:50 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Earthquake occurred last evening wide area central and southern Mexico.
                            One person reported killed and 25 injured and over 50 buildings
                            seriously damaged this city. Believe no American citizens or American
                            interest suffered.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Frazer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>